  "text": "The worldwide obesity epidemic together with related pathologies such as type 2 diabetes mellitus (T2DM) and increased risk of cardiovascular mortality and morbidity has underscored the need for effective, reliable and simple weight-reduction strategies (O'Rahilly 1997, [CITATION_1] . Despite intensive efforts, the search for a pharmacological approach able to effectively decrease body weight and improve metabolic complications still continues. The only strategy proven to induce sustainable reduction of body weight in patients with a high degree of obesity remains surgical treatment [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Although major metabolic improvements are evident in all patients after bariatric surgery, various types of operations differ in the rate of diabetes remission and in the timing of metabolic improvements [CITATION_4] .",
